[{"text": "I learned about the Haiti earthquake by Skype.", "start": 16.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "My wife sent me a message,", "start": 19.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "\"Whoa, earthquake,\"", "start": 22.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and then disappeared for 25 minutes.", "start": 24.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It was 25 minutes of absolute terror", "start": 28.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that thousands of people across the U.S. felt.", "start": 31.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "I was afraid of a tsunami;", "start": 36.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "what I didn't realize", "start": 39.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "was there was a greater terror in Haiti,", "start": 41.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and that was building collapse.", "start": 44.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "We've all seen the photos", "start": 47.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the collapsed buildings in Haiti.", "start": 49.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "These are shots my wife took", "start": 52.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "a couple days after the quake,", "start": 54.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "while I was making my way through the D.R. into the country.", "start": 56.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This is the national palace --", "start": 60.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the equivalent of the White House.", "start": 62.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This is the largest supermarket in the Caribbean", "start": 65.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "at peak shopping time.", "start": 68.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This is a nurses' college --", "start": 73.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "there are 300 nurses studying.", "start": 75.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The general hospital right next door", "start": 79.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "emerged largely unscathed.", "start": 81.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This is the Ministry of Economics and Finance.", "start": 84.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "We have all heard", "start": 90.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "about the tremendous human loss", "start": 92.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "in the earthquake in Haiti,", "start": 95.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but we haven't heard enough", "start": 97.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "about why all those lives were lost.", "start": 100.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "We haven't heard about", "start": 103.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "why the buildings failed.", "start": 105.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "After all, it was the buildings,", "start": 108.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "not the earthquake,", "start": 110.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that killed 220,000 people,", "start": 112.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that injured 330,000,", "start": 115.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that displaced 1.3 million people,", "start": 118.26, "duration": 5.0}, {"text": "that cut off food", "start": 124.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and water and supplies", "start": 126.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for an entire nation.", "start": 128.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "This is the largest metropolitan-area disaster", "start": 131.26, "duration": 5.0}, {"text": "in decades,", "start": 136.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and it was not a natural disaster --", "start": 139.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "it was a disaster of engineering.", "start": 142.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "AIDG has worked in Haiti", "start": 145.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "since 2007,", "start": 147.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "providing engineering and business support", "start": 149.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to small businesses.", "start": 151.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And after the quake, we started bringing in earthquake engineers", "start": 153.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "to figure out why the buildings collapsed,", "start": 157.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to examine what was safe and what wasn't.", "start": 159.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Working with MINUSTAH,", "start": 162.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "which is the U.N. mission in Haiti,", "start": 165.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "with the Ministry of Public Works,", "start": 167.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "with different NGOs,", "start": 169.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "we inspected over 1,500 buildings.", "start": 171.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "We inspected schools", "start": 175.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and private residencies.", "start": 177.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We inspected medical centers", "start": 179.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and food warehouses.", "start": 181.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "We inspected government buildings.", "start": 183.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "This is the Ministry of Justice.", "start": 185.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Behind that door", "start": 187.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is the National Judicial Archives.", "start": 189.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The fellow in the door, Andre Filitrault --", "start": 192.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "who's the director", "start": 194.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the Center for Interdisciplinary Earthquake Engineering Research", "start": 196.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "at the University of Buffalo --", "start": 200.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "was examining it to see if it was safe", "start": 203.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to recover the archives.", "start": 205.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Andre told me,", "start": 207.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "after seeing these buildings fail", "start": 209.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "again and again in the same way,", "start": 211.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that there is no new research here.", "start": 214.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "There is nothing here that we don't know.", "start": 217.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The failure points were the same:", "start": 220.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "walls and slabs not tied properly into columns --", "start": 223.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "that's a roof slab hanging off the building --", "start": 226.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "cantilevered structures,", "start": 231.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "or structures that were asymmetric,", "start": 233.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that shook violently and came down,", "start": 235.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "poor building materials,", "start": 239.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "not enough concrete,", "start": 241.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "not enough compression in the blocks,", "start": 243.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "rebar that was smooth,", "start": 247.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "rebar that was exposed to the weather and had rusted away.", "start": 249.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Now there's a solution", "start": 252.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to all these problems.", "start": 255.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And we know how to build properly.", "start": 257.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The proof of this came in Chile,", "start": 260.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "almost a month later,", "start": 263.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "when 8.8 magnitude earthquake", "start": 266.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "hit Chile.", "start": 270.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "That is 500 times", "start": 272.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the power of the 7.0", "start": 274.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that hit Port-au-Prince --", "start": 276.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "500 times the power,", "start": 279.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "yet only under a thousand casualties.", "start": 281.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Adjusted for population density,", "start": 286.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that is less than one percent", "start": 288.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "of the impact of the Haitian quake.", "start": 290.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "What was the difference", "start": 294.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "between Chile and Haiti?", "start": 296.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Seismic standards", "start": 299.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and confined masonry,", "start": 301.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "where the building acts as a whole --", "start": 304.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "walls and columns", "start": 306.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and roofs and slabs", "start": 308.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "tied together to support each other --", "start": 310.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "instead of breaking off into separate members and failing.", "start": 313.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "If you look at this building in Chile,", "start": 318.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "it's ripped in half,", "start": 321.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but it's not a pile of rubble.", "start": 323.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Chileans have been building with confined masonry", "start": 327.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for decades.", "start": 329.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Right now, AIDG is working with KPFF Consulting Engineers,", "start": 332.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "Architecture for Humanity,", "start": 336.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to bring more confined masonry training", "start": 338.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "into Haiti.", "start": 341.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "This is Xantus Daniel;", "start": 345.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "he's a mason,", "start": 347.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "just a general construction worker, not a foreman,", "start": 349.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "who took one of our trainings.", "start": 352.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "On his last job he was working with his boss,", "start": 354.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and they started pouring the columns wrong.", "start": 357.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "He took his boss aside,", "start": 360.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and he showed him the materials on confined masonry.", "start": 362.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "He showed him, \"You know, we don't have to do this wrong.", "start": 365.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "It won't cost us any more", "start": 368.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to do it the right way.\"", "start": 370.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "And they redid that building.", "start": 373.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "They tied the rebar right,", "start": 375.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "they poured the columns right,", "start": 377.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and that building will be safe.", "start": 379.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And every building", "start": 381.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that they build going forward", "start": 383.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "will be safe.", "start": 385.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "To make sure these buildings are safe,", "start": 388.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it's not going to take policy --", "start": 390.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "it's going to take reaching out", "start": 393.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to the masons on the ground", "start": 395.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "and helping them learn the proper techniques.", "start": 398.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Now there are many groups doing this.", "start": 403.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "And the fellow in the vest there,", "start": 405.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "Craig Toten,", "start": 407.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "he has pushed forward", "start": 409.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to get documentation out to all the groups that are doing this.", "start": 411.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Through Haiti Rewired,", "start": 415.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "through Build Change, Architecture for Humanity,", "start": 417.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "AIDG,", "start": 420.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "there is the possibility", "start": 422.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "to reach out", "start": 424.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to 30,000 -- 40,000 masons", "start": 427.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "across the country", "start": 430.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and create a movement of proper building.", "start": 432.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "If you reach out to the people on the ground", "start": 437.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "in this collaborative way", "start": 439.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "it's extremely affordable.", "start": 441.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "For the billions spent on reconstruction,", "start": 444.26, "duration": 4.0}, {"text": "you can train masons", "start": 448.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for dollars on every house", "start": 450.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that they end up building over their lifetime.", "start": 452.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "Ultimately, there are two ways", "start": 457.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that you can rebuild Haiti;", "start": 459.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the way at the top", "start": 461.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is the way that Haiti's been building for decades.", "start": 463.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "The way at the top", "start": 466.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "is a poorly constructed building", "start": 468.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "that will fail.", "start": 470.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "The way at the bottom is a confined masonry building,", "start": 472.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "where the walls are tied together,", "start": 475.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "the building is symmetric,", "start": 477.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "and it will stand up to an earthquake.", "start": 479.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "For all the disaster,", "start": 482.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "there is an opportunity here", "start": 484.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "to build better houses", "start": 487.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "for the next generation,", "start": 489.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "so that when the next earthquake hits,", "start": 491.26, "duration": 3.0}, {"text": "it is a disaster --", "start": 494.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "but not a tragedy.", "start": 496.26, "duration": 2.0}, {"text": "(Applause)", "start": 499.26, "duration": 4.0}]